					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-569510#post-1575226</guid>
				<title>Here goes nothing...</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-569510/scp-1702#post-1575226</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 27 Sep 2012 20:46:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Aelanna</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>334454</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This one is a bit of an experiment which I quite honestly don't know if I've hit the sweet spot on. The inspiration came from a conversation in the SCP staff channel in which we discovered a little-known fact about bees: a queen bee is pampered and has her every need tended to&#8230; so long as she remains productive and &quot;undamaged&quot;. The moment she becomes unable to produce proper offspring, if she loses a leg or antennae or if the pheromones she produces become &quot;off&quot;, her loyal subjects turn on her, tear her apart and proceed to &quot;modify&quot; an already-laid egg in preparation to produce a new resident queen. A few of us considered the horror if the queen were actually a sentient, sapient being and thus this idea came into being.</p> <p>On a completely separate note, Mr Wilt has informed me that today is the first anniversary of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/bees">Bee Day</a>. Talk about coincidences&#8230;</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
